  • All applicants must provide documentation of their completed undergraduate degree (a bachelor's degree or its equivalent) from a regionally accredited institution prior to matriculation. (Applicants who have not completed their bachelor's degree by the time they submit their application for admission may be admitted to CMU Australia with the condition they submit their final transcript#Comma including their date of graduation#Comma prior to the start of their first semester at CMU Australia.) For the Graduate Certificate in BIDA and the Advanced Certificate in BIDA applicants need a recently completed IT undergraduate degree. If applicants do not have this but have 3 or more years of recent professional IT work experience they are still eligible to apply.

  • You are required to sit the CMU Institutional Maths Online Test. About CMU IMOT: 1.The test is free of charge. 2. It is a one hour test comprising 32 multiple choice questions. The topics include basic algebra#Comma calculus and statistics calculations. 3.The test can only be taken once and you will need to achieve a minimum score of 75%.
    • #Newline
  • You are required to submit valid test results from either the GRE (General Test) or the GMAT from within the last 5 years#Comma or sit for CMU Institutional Maths Online Test. For applicants taking CMU Institutional Maths Online Test CMU Institutional Maths Online Test (IMOT) is available as a substitute for GRE and GMAT for CMUA programs (except global programs). About CMU IMOT: 1. The test is free of charge. 2. It is a one hour test comprising 32 multiple choice questions. The topics include basic algebra#Comma calculus and statistics calculations. 3. The test can only be taken once and you will need to achieve a minimum score of 75%. For applicants taking GRE or GMAT Students must achieve an average minimum score of GRE 300 and GMAT 600. The test scores must be reported directly by the testing service. The Education Testing Service (ETS) administers the GRE (www.ets.org/gre). The Graduate Management Admissions Council (GMAC) administers the GMAT (www.mba.com). We recommend that applicants take the GMAT or GRE at least one month prior to the application deadline (please see Application Deadline information within each program's admissions requirements section). Please note there is no preference between the GRE or the GMAT for our Masters' programs.
    • #Newline

column2: HOW TO APPLY FOR THE IMOT
column5: 1. Submit your online application. 2. After you have submitted your application#Comma send your request to sit for CMU IMOT to admissions@australia.cmu.edu. 3. CMUA admissions team will then get back to you with the instructions on how to take the test.

column2: HOW TO REPORT THE GRE OR GMAT SCORE TO US
column5: 1. Order an official score report from the testing service to be sent directly to CMU Australia (see codes listed below). You may submit scores from up to 2 valid GRE or GMAT exam dates test dates. CMU Australia will use the highest score verified in each section if you have taken the exam more than one time. For every score you wish to include with your application#Comma you must submit the official score report(s) via the testing service. We will not accept exam scores for test dates that are not listed on the application. 2. On the online application#Comma enter the exam date for every exam you want to report to us. Enter as much additional information as possible#Comma including registration number for the GRE or exam appointment number for the GMAT. Note that the only required information is the exam date. We will not verify scores for exam dates that are not listed on your application. 3. If available#Comma please upload a copy of your score report(s) to the application (screen shot of online score report is fine. If you do not have a copy of your score report when you submit your online application#Comma please email a copy of your score report to us (admissions@australia.cmu.edu) after you receive access to it (screen shot is fine). Uploading or sending a copy of your score report does not replace the requirement of ordering an official report from the testing service#Comma but it may help us verify your scores more quickly. Please have your scores sent to the CMU Australia using the following codes. GMAT: MSIT 12-month: 69H-V8-75 MSIT-ITM 21-month: 69H-V8-75 MSIT-BIDA 21-month: 69H-V8-75 MSPPM 12-month: 69H-V8-77 MSPPM 21-month: 69H-V8-77	GRE: 7359

It is strongly recommended for applicants to take the TOEFL or IELTS at least one month prior to the application deadline..   • You may complete a video interview with your application for admission. The video interview is optional#Comma but it is strongly recommended for non-native speakers of English. We are unable to watch videos that come in any form other than a URL link. We will not accept videos sent by email or on DVD through the mail. We have the instruction of the video interview.

  • You may complete a video interview with your application for admission. The video interview is optional#Comma but it is strongly recommended for non-native speakers of English. We are happy to now offer an automated#Comma online video interview to all applicants as a preferred alternative to submitting the optional video essay#Comma particularly for non-native speakers of English. Please Note: After you begin the video interview#Comma you will not be able to pause#Comma cancel or re-record any of your answers. Please keep this in mind as you decide when and where to complete your video interview. The video (and audio) must be of you#Comma the applicant (not a proxy). Video Essay: If you decide to submit a video essay#Comma please prepare a one-minute-long video that lets the admission committee know who you are#Comma what you do well#Comma and what you are looking to achieve in your graduate study at the CMU Australia. Please note that the video must be of the you#Comma the applicant (not a proxy). If there is more than one person in the video#Comma please clarify which person is you#Comma the applicant. What you do or say is totally up to you as long as you provide the information requested. Upload the video to an easily accessible website (such as YouTube) and give us the URL and any required access codes in the appropriate fields within the application for admission. It is the applicant’s responsibility to correctly configure the security and access settings for the video. We recommend that the applicant use the strongest privacy settings available while still allowing access to the CMU Australia. If using YouTube#Comma we suggest using the “Unlisted Video” setting so that only individuals who have the URL can view it. The applicant is also responsible for adhering to the terms and conditions of the website used to share the video essay. Following evaluation of the video essay#Comma CMU Australia will retain a short excerpt or screen shot of the video as a part of the official student record. We are unable to watch videos that come in any form other than a URL link. We will not accept videos sent by email or on DVD through the mail. We have the instruction of the video interview.
    • #Newline

column2: THE INSTRUCTION OF THE VIDEO INTERVIEW
column5: Instructions: Please click on the Check-In URL on the Essays and Uploads page of the online application to begin your interview. The link should appear within ten minutes of completing and saving the Degree Information page in your application. You will also receive an email invitation from Kira Talent with this Check-In URL. Please refresh your browser if the URL is not yet visible. The Check-In URL will remain available after you submit your online application. If you wish to include a video interview with your application#Comma please complete the video interview no later than 7 days after you submit the online application.#NewlineHere is what you can expect if you complete the video interview:#Newline1. You will first receive instructions and the system will help you ensure that your computer is set up correctly to begin the interview.#Newline2. You will then have a chance to answer two randomised practice questions an unlimited number of times to become comfortable with the system. Immediately after responding to each practice question#Comma you will have a chance to watch your practice video. (Your practice videos will not be saved nor will they be sent to Carnegie Mellon University.)#Newline3. When you begin the actual interview#Comma you will be asked three (3) randomised questions.#Newline4. After you see and hear the question#Comma you will have 20 seconds to think about your answer.#Newline5. After the preparation time ends#Comma your computer will automatically begin to record your answer.#Newline6. You will have 60 seconds to provide each answer. You will have only one chance to answer each question.#Newline7. You will not be able to pause the interview after it starts.#Newline8. You will not be able to re-record any answer after the interview begins.#Newline9. You may complete your video interview before or after you submit the online application#Comma but you will only be able to complete the interview one time. If you want to ensure that your video interview is reviewed by the admissions committee#Comma please be sure to complete your interview within 7 days after you submit the online application (at the latest).#Newline10. Just like a real#Comma live interview#Comma you will not be able to view your answer to any questions nor will you be able to view your completed interview.#NewlineAt the conclusion of your interview#Comma you will see a very short Thank You video to confirm your video submission. You will also receive a confirmation email from Kira Talent after your video interview has been completed. Your video interview will automatically be added to your online application. If you have not submitted your online application at the time that you record your video interview#Comma please remember to complete and submit your online application after recording your interview.

  • >All applicants are required to have two (2) recommendation forms submitted on their behalf. Recommendations should be provided from employers#Comma supervisors#Comma professors#Comma or others who are able to comment on your professional and educational goals and potential. At least one (1) of your recommenders should know you in a professional setting (full-time employment#Comma internship#Comma part-time employment#Comma research#Comma non-academic extracurricular activity#Comma etc.) You may opt to have up to three (3) recommendations submitted in support of your application. Please note: recommendations from friends#Comma family members or acquaintances#Comma and other sources not able to evaluate applicants on an academic or professional basis#Comma will not be accepted. Recommendations are submitted electronically through the online application system by your recommenders. We do not accept recommendations submitted on paper. You must enter the names and contact information for each recommendation provider into the application system. Prior to requesting that your recommendation providers complete the recommendation online#Comma be sure to check with them to ensure that you register them with the correct (preferably professional) email address. Please let your recommenders know that they may upload an electronic document or scanned copy of a paper-based recommendation using the online system rather than using the text box response fields (but they must upload their recommendation via the online system). Each recommender may be asked sereval questions.

column2: THE QUESTIONS THAT MAY BE ASKED TO THE RECOMMENDORS
column5: 1. How long and in what capacity have you known the applicant?  Please clearly indicate your position in relation to the applicant (i.e. - professor/instructor#Comma direct supervisor#Comma mentor#Comma advisor#Comma colleague#Comma etc.).#Newline2. Do you believe the applicant gives her/his maximum effort and perseveres towards the stated goal when given a task#Comma assignment or project?  Please provide details to support your answer.#Newline3. Discuss how the applicant works in a group (including interpersonal skills) and/or functions in a leadership role.#Newline4. Describe the applicant's ability to communicate in oral and written form.#Newline5. Provide an example where the applicant worked to solve a problem or handled a difficult situation in a professional manner.#Newline6. If you are able#Comma please describe the applicant's understanding of#Comma background in and commitment to this academic/professional field.#Newline7.Please share any additional information about the applicant’s personal qualities#Comma maturity#Comma academic or professional record which you believe would be helpful to the admissions committee.#Newline8. Please select your overall recommendation regarding this individual's application for admission for graduate study at Carnegie Mellon University. (Recommenders must select one of these responses: Strongly recommend#Comma Recommend#Comma Recommend with reservations#Comma Do not recommend.)

  • CMU Australia is committed to ensuring the integrity of our admissions process and the reputation of our educational programs. We also want to protect and enhance the value of the degrees that we confer. All enrolling students will be required to successfully complete a verification process of their admission application materials. The verification process will be completed by an outside#Comma independent contractor hired by the Heinz College and Carnegie Mellon University. The purpose of this background check is to protect all stakeholders of the program (students#Comma faculty#Comma staff and alumni) from those who would falsify their backgrounds to gain an unfair advantage in the admissions process. We have made the decision to implement an independent verification process of all application materials for any master's student enrolling at CMU Australia. We believe that this verification will support our efforts to ensure integrity throughout the program. Upon admission#Comma you will receive more details about this process. Students who have accepted the offer of admission will be contacted by the Office of Admissions regarding the verification process prior to the start of their first semester.
    • #Newline

All programs (except global) If your application is complete and no further information is required#Comma your application will be assessed in approximately 2 to 3 weeks. Global programs Your application will be assessed within 2 to 3 months after the application closing date.

If you have done all of the above and are still having issues#Comma please contact us on admissions@australia.cmu.edu and we can further assist you.
You can ask me: 1. information about CMUA program. 2. Program in CMUA and Pittsburgh. 3. Issue about leaving or terminating.

You can ask me: 1. Can international students take the Graduate Certificate or Advanced Diploma in BIDA? 2. Does CMUA offer a PhD program? 3. Will I gain credit for my prior studies? 4.Will there be evening classes?
Currently the Graduate Certificate and the Advanced Diploma in BIDA are only offered to Australian citizens and Permanent Residents.
There are no PhD programs available at Carnegie Mellon University in Australia.  However#Comma many of our graduates go on to PhD programs at leading universities around the world.

Carnegie Mellon University may grant credit or advanced standing or exemptions for subjects or qualifications completed at other tertiary institutions within Australia#Comma USA or overseas.   Applications for credit or exemptions are usually assessed upon enrolment and in most cases you will need to provide detailed subject descriptions for an assessment to be undertaken.

We do offer some courses in the evening#Comma however this is not applicable to all courses. Please check the website:https://www.australia.cmu.edu/student-experience/current-students for more information

You can ask me: 1. What is the difference between the programs in Adelaide and Pittsburgh? 2.Can I transfer from a CMUA program to a program in Pittsburgh? 3. Do I study the same curriculum taught by CMU faculty?

Programs run in Adelaide and Pittsburgh deliver the same curriculum#Comma allowing our students the opportunity to take courses from faculty across the global CMU network#Comma to receive the same degree#Comma and to enjoy the same alumni connections.  Global programs conclude with two semesters in Pittsburgh#Comma while all other programs are completely conducted in Adelaide.
Students are unable to transfer from the Australian programs to the global programs or another program in Pittsburgh.
Students study the same world-class CMU curriculum and are taught by faculty employed by CMU.
You can ask me: 1. Can I take leave or withdraw from my study? 2.Can the university suspend or terminate my enrollment?

If you wish to take leave or withdraw from your course at the University#Comma you should contact the Senior Director of Academic and Institutional Development to discuss your circumstances as soon as possible. To withdraw from your course#Comma you will need to formally notify the University by contacting the Admissions office.

They can suspend or terminate your program#Comma and for International students#Comma The University must notify the Australian Government of student visa holders whose enrollment has been suspended or terminated#Comma The government may cancel your student visa if your enrollment is terminated as a result of misconduct or unsatisfactory academic progress#Comma Students who no longer study in Australia must depart Australia or apply for another visa within 28 days of the enrollment cancellation date or before their visa expires#Comma Contact the Australian Government for further information
